  "prompt": "What type of antenna is used in mobile phone receivers?",
  "response": "Mobile phone receivers typically use a type of antenna known as a **microstrip antenna**, also referred to as a **patch antenna**. These antennas are popular in mobile devices due to their compact size, lightweight design, and ability to be integrated easily with circuit boards. \n\nIn addition to microstrip antennas, mobile phones may also use:\n\n1. **Internal antennas**: These are often embedded within the phone's casing, helping to maintain a sleek design while providing reliable communication.\n\n2. **Diversity antennas**: Some mobile devices use multiple antennas to improve signal reception and reduce interference. This helps the phone maintain a better connection in varying environments.\n\n3. **Loop antennas**: These may also be utilized in some mobile devices for specific functions, such as NFC (Near Field Communication) capabilities.\n\nOverall, the specific type of antenna can vary by manufacturer and device model, but microstrip or patch antennas are the most common for general mobile communication purposes (such as cellular networks).",
